#week-title("One", "The Mineral Mercury Distinguished from Common Quicksilver")

=== Core Teaching

The Philosophic Mercury of the mineral kingdom — called variously the Sophie
Mercury, the Mineral Mercury, or simply the Mercury of the Philosophers — is
not common quicksilver (liquid mercury, Hg). This confusion has misled
practitioners throughout the tradition's history and continues to mislead.

Common quicksilver is the physical metal mercury: dense, liquid, volatile, toxic.
It is the physical expression of the Mercury principle in the mineral kingdom,
just as vegetable alcohol is the physical expression of the Mercury principle
in the vegetable kingdom. But in neither case is the physical substance the
same as the philosophic principle it represents.

The Philosophic Mercury of the mineral kingdom is the *universal volatile
principle prepared from minerals themselves* — extracted, purified, and
concentrated through the operations of the Via Humida or Via Sicca, until
it possesses the capacity to dissolve and transmute other mineral substances.
It is the mineral kingdom's analogue of the rectified spirit of wine: the
highest expression of the volatile, Mercury principle, now operating at the
mineral vibratory level.

The preparation of the Philosophic Mineral Mercury is the central practical
achievement toward which the entire Year Three mineral work builds. The student
who has completed the Via Humida cycles of Month 2 and the advanced antimony
preparations of Months 1–3 has laid the groundwork for understanding what
this Mercury is and how it is prepared.

*The three principles in the mineral kingdom — their expression:*

- *Mineral Mercury (volatile/spirit):* The acidic, volatile, mobile fraction —
  what rises in mineral distillation; the spirit of the metal; what is extracted
  by the dissolving acid medium in the Via Humida.
- *Mineral Sulphur (soul):* The combustible, colouring, characterising fraction
  — the fire within the mineral; what burns and produces the characteristic
  colour and smell of roasted ores.
- *Mineral Salt (body):* The fixed, non-volatile residue — the ash after
  calcination; the crystalline structure that holds the mineral's form.

These three are separated by the Via Humida operations already underway. What
Month 3 adds is the deliberate attention to identifying each fraction precisely
and understanding what it is and what it will do.

